    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-11-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="197"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Webb</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 238.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-11-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 17, 1868.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your dispatch of the 8th ultimo, without number,
                    has been received. The recent events in Paraguay to which it refers may be
                    regarded as painfully important. The letter<note n="*" xml:id="d197fn1">For this
                        inclosure see instructions to Mr. Washburn, No. 78, November 17,
                        1868.</note> of this department to the Secretary of the Navy, a copy of
                    which is inclosed, has been approved by the President, and may be accepted as
                    our present impression in regard to affairs in that quarter. Any further
                    measures which may be considered or adopted will depend upon future
                    developments.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James Watson Webb,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
